  "text": "Mosquitoes from the F1 generation were screened for infection with WNV by either SYBRH Green (Quantitect SYBRH Green reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction [RT-PCR] kit, QIAGEN) or TaqMan (QuantiTect Probe RT-PCR, QIAGEN) RT-PCR [CITATION_1] . For SYBR Green RT-PCR, a 2-ml volume of extracted RNA from individual mosquito bodies or legs was introduced into a 20-ml RT-PCR reaction containing 1 mM each of WNV envelope glycoprotein gene (WNENV)-forward and WNENV-reverse primers and reaction components recommended by the manufacturer. Amplification conditions were an initial cycle of 30 min at 50 C for reverse transcription, 15 min at 95 C for initial PCR activation, followed by 40 cycles consisting of a 15-sec denaturation at 94 C, a 30-sec annealing at 50 C, and a 30-sec extension at 72 C. For TaqMan RT-PCR, the same volume of extracted RNA was introduced into a 20-ml RT-PCR reaction containing 1 mM each of WNENV-forward and WNENV-reverse primers, 0.25 mM WNENV-probe , and reaction components recommended by the manufacturer. Amplification conditions consisted of an initial cycle of 30 min at 50 C for reverse transcription, 15 min at 95 C for initial PCR activation, followed by 40 cycles with a 15-sec denaturation step at 94 C, a 60-sec annealing and extension step at 60 C. All samples were amplified on an ABI PrismH 7000 Detection System (Applied Biosystems, Foster City, California, USA).",
